# cire-api origin. Dev default below; production builds set
# PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.cireweddings.com. The guest site is SSR (Astro on
# Cloudflare Pages), so this is read per-request server-side and by the islands.
PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8787
# Guest site canonical URL (used in <link rel="canonical"> / share metadata).
# Production: https://cireweddings.com (apex). Leave unset locally.
PUBLIC_SITE_URL=
# NOTE: there is no PUBLIC_WEDDING_SLUG any more. The guest site is server-rendered
# and resolves which wedding to show FROM THE PATH (`/<wedding-slug>`); the bare
# domain (`/`) resolves the primary wedding via `GET /api/primary-wedding` and
# redirects to its path. No build-time wedding slug is baked in.
# Optional. Google Maps Platform key with the *Maps Embed API* enabled. When set,
# the event "Where" section renders a real Maps Embed iframe (free, unlimited,
# queried by the free-text venue address — no coordinates). When unset/blank, the
# page falls back to the CSS-drawn map card, so this is a pure enhancement.
# This key bakes into static HTML at build time, so it MUST be referrer-restricted
# to the guest-site origin(s) at the Maps Platform console.
PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_EMBED_KEY=
# Optional. Cloudflare Turnstile sitekey (PUBLIC — safe to embed in client HTML).
# When set, the guest claim + RSVP forms render the Turnstile bot-challenge and
# gate submit on it, and the cire-api Worker enforces siteverify (set the matching
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY there via `wrangler secret put`). When unset/blank, no
# widget renders and no siteverify runs — key-optional, so this is a pure
# enhancement. Bakes into static HTML at build time. Create the widget at
# Cloudflare dash → Turnstile (domains: cireweddings.com + app.cireweddings.com).
PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITEKEY=
